Track Location Using Phone Number

A Python application to track the location of a phone number and display it on an interactive map.

ğŸ“œ Summary
This project demonstrates how to use Python libraries such as phonenumbers, opencage, and folium to:
Determine the location of a phone number.
Fetch the latitude and longitude of the location using the OpenCage API.
Display the location on an interactive map.
âš ï¸ Note: This app only fetches the general location based on the phone number's registered region. It does NOT provide live GPS tracking or violate privacy laws.

ğŸš€ Features
Identify the location of a phone number (country/region).
Determine the carrier (service provider).
Visualize the location on a map using Folium.
Save the generated map as an HTML file for sharing or offline use.

